review_blob: freaking awesome. huge hop aroma, hops over power the strong malt presence, exactly what i like in a double ipa. more please. thanks Andrew!
faint aroma, but some hops. very heavy on the palate. chocolate, coffee, black licorice with a nice bitter finish. well done Taps.
not spectacular by any means, but a pretty good easy drinking beer with a hit of mild hops. pretty good for the style
beer_name: Lake of Bays Spark House Red

review_blob: got a lot of the spruce in the aroma but none in the flavour. caramel, molasses and booze mostly. pretty good.
black pour, not really any head. mostly tasted black licorice, raisins and booze. not a fan of black licorice so i didnt really like this beer.
on tap. as others have mentioned, this shouldnt really be in the ipa category. pretty well done though, nice fruity hopiness throughout and a light crisp bitter finish.
beer_name: Double Trouble Hops and Robbers IPA

review_blob: not bad, just not great. grainy, bready maybea hint of caramel. slight hop finish. no where near as good as the blackened IPA beer these two breweries did.

light brown pour, small head. slight hop aroma. a little sweet, caramelly and bready to start with a nice citrus hop finish. well balanced. nothing too overpowering. turned out pretty good, will have to grab a few more.
was okay. its tough too make a good beer in this style, wasnt bad by any means. better than most of that garbage at the beer store.
wasnt too impressed with this one. there simply wasnt anything too it. better than their stock ale though lol
heavy molasses looking pour with some head. a bit of raisins and other dried fruit. very drinkable. pretty good.
noticably lighter than most big stouts but it tasted much heavier than a 5% beer.
taste was like a blue freezee. wasnt bad by any means just a little to sweet for my liking
not undrinkable by any means, just nothing to really talk about. i guess better than most macro stuff around herre
this was a real treat, thanks Andrew!. i didnt think a beer with that many blends would turn out to be anything but this really surprised me. too many subtleties to mention... it just worked.
had the Zomer right before this one which was a mistake as the zomer blew this out of the water. still a great gueze though!
kudos to Church Key for this one, havnt had much from them that I like, this was actaully quite good
17th. another highly anticipated beer from this brewer, and another disapointment. maybe were just getting older bottles  or something.
beer_name: Great Divide Anniversary Wood Aged Double IPA

review_blob: needs age. way way too sweet. couldnt get past the sweetness to really appreciate this one.
beer_name: Cigar City Warmer Winter Winter Warmer

review_blob: we had a bottle that was aged over a year and it turned out great. this beer is incredibly underrated.
wasnt a terribly exciting beer but it wasnt bad at the same time. some spices kept it interesting
green cap. i guess the best way to explain it would be to say its like the normal BORIS with a hit of bourbon. turned out great though!
beer_name: Hoppin Frog Barrel Aged BORIS The Crusher

review_blob: another great example of the style. im typically not a huge fan of the oatmeal stouts but this one really did it for me.
over the top hop aroma on this one, not a bad thing, just not what im expecting for an impy stout. great beer though, bourbon and vanilla comes through nicely

jet black, very thick pour. all the characteristics one would want in a stout, coffee, chocolate some licorice and fruityness. amazing that the alcohol is above 15%, you do get a bit of burn but it just adds to the complexity. thanks to Andrew for this one.
not bad, light and a slight hop kick as expected. just nothing to special about it

incredible "sourish" aroma. cloudy golden pour with huge head. intense sour taste, with a lot of different fruits. everything i want from a sour, this was awesome. huge thanks to Andrew, definitely worth the $
Nothing to special, I may age a few to see if they improve. Incredibly drinkable though, not even a hint of alcohol.
not sure who brought this, but thanks. overall was decent. had a lot of mediocre belgian ales this night, and this was just another one.
my only tasting note was meh not bad so must have been at the end of the night.
not very good for a triple. not a lot of flavour, some raisin i guess. not terrible just not something i would have again
this wasnt bad, just wasnt much too it. some spices were noticable but beyond that it was pretty boring
typical belgian ale. nothing too special about it. a little thin on the mouthfeel
huge pumpkin pie aroma. orange pour with little head. mouthfeel was a little thin. pumpkin, cinnamon and nutmeg all noticable. alcohol was quite evident.
some chocolate and coffee. didnt get any roastiness. very sweet. not bad just not very good either.
Caramel and booze on the nose. Black pour with thin head. Flavor was almost a perfect example if the style... Like a light stout. A little watery though

can from the brewery. black pour, with some head but not much. chocolate quite evident in the aroma. lots of roast chocolate with some coffee. a little sweeter than expected. alcohol completely hidden (no burn at all) didnt get any peppermint. got a hint of the balsam fir. overall a great stout. nice job!
Roast coffee and chocolate aroma. Black pour with small head. Taste matched the aroma. A little thinner than expected but still a very good brew
Black pour with Lots of roast iness, very good. Cant remember much else
Heavy roast chocolate aroma. Gorgeous jet black pour with a large dark mocha head that retains. Coffee, chocolate and some roastiness with a slight bitterness. Well done
big fruity hop aroma. dark copperish pour. dark fruits, cherries, caramel with a nice bitter finish. awesome beer.
bottle. orangish pour, faint citrus hop aroma. fairly good example of an english style IPA (or ESB per RB). hops not overpowering but noticable. not bad
Roasty chocolate aroma, black pour with big tan head. Some nice chocolate flavors but it had a distinct rice flavor. Bonus points for being so cheap though
Just another attempt from this brewery, not as bad a there others but not good either
This was amazing, I only wish I didnt have it closer to the end of the night so I could remember more about it. My only tasting note was awesome
Awesome for a lighter belgian, had all the expected flavors but was a little more drinkable than others in the style. Well done
Pretty good, lots of fruit, mostly cherry. some darker malty flavor. Pretty good, would have again
beer_name: Certified Originals Rudolphs Red Nose Ale

review_blob: a little more flavor than most wits, pretty good.  Spices add.  some nice flavors as well, one of the better wits Ive had
beer_name: Great Lakes Holy Moses White Ale

review_blob: Cloudy yellow. banana aroma. Banana with some raisin, a little cherry, overall pretty good
beer_name: Samuel Adams (Barrel Room Collection) New World Tripel

review_blob: Hoppy grainy with some licorice aroma . Very roasty flavor, not what if expect from a dipa but not bad. Just no where near hoppy enough for my taste
